            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13075",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Assign to Alexander.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-01T16:17:35.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-01T16:17:35.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13954",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alexander",
                        "name": "alexander",
                        "displayName": "Alexander Veremyev",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Zend_Search_Lucene_Analysis_Analyzer class uses leafs of hierarchy.\n\nIt's actually only one class (Zend_Search_Lucene_Analysis_Analyzer_Common_Text_CaseInsensitive), but any other may be used.\nSo it needs circular require_once().\n\nWhole hierarchy has to be used through including Zend\/Search\/Lucene\/Analysis\/Analyzer.php file:\n{code}\nrequire_once 'Zend\/Search\/Lucene\/Analysis\/Analyzer.php';\n{code}\n\nIt guarantees all files are loaded\/parsed in right order. (I've just corrected example in the documentation)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alexander",
                        "name": "alexander",
                        "displayName": "Alexander Veremyev",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-04-04T07:33:53.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-04-04T07:33:53.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/18812",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=twk",
                        "name": "twk",
                        "displayName": "twk",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I don't think it's obvious you must require Analyzer.php instead of the class to use.\nYou know http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/browse\/ZF-2456 is posted from the same origin.\n\nI am not sure if Zend_Search_Lucene_Analysis_Analyzer REALLY needs leafs of hierarchy,\nbut if it does, the change like the following would fix the problem.\n\n- Move require_once's at the beginning of Analyzer.php and put them into the new file (name it A.php).\n- Analyzer.php and all leaf classes SHOULD requires A.php instead of the classes to use.\n\nIn short, odd things (requiring the non-obvious file) should be done by the framework, not by the frame work user.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=twk",
                        "name": "twk",
                        "displayName": "twk",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-04T06:19:47.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-04T06:19:47.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
